# Quantum ESPRESSO setup

This project uses Quantum ESPRESSO (QE) 7.5 for targeted DFT validation after MLIP screening. QE is open-source and replaces the earlier VASP-based plan.

## Installation (Linux)

Build dependencies (Ubuntu/Debian):
```
sudo apt-get install -y gfortran libopenmpi-dev libblas-dev liblapack-dev libfftw3-dev
```

Download, extract, and build:
```
mkdir -p ~/software && cd ~/software
curl -L -o qe-7.5-ReleasePack.tar.gz \
  "https://www.quantum-espresso.org/rdm-download/8/v7-5/c660239520162325dd0c670ba0a4b65c/qe-7.5-ReleasePack.tar.gz"
tar xzf qe-7.5-ReleasePack.tar.gz && cd qe-7.5
./configure && make -j$(nproc) pw
echo 'export PATH="$HOME/software/qe-7.5/bin:$PATH"' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc
```

Verify: `pw.x --version` should print `Program PWSCF v.7.5`.

## Pseudopotentials

Download PBE PAW pseudopotentials from the QE library:
```
mkdir -p ~/software/pseudopotentials/pbe && cd ~/software/pseudopotentials/pbe
curl -L -O "https://pseudopotentials.quantum-espresso.org/upf_files/Co.pbe-spn-kjpaw_psl.0.3.1.UPF"
curl -L -O "https://pseudopotentials.quantum-espresso.org/upf_files/Bi.pbe-dn-kjpaw_psl.1.0.0.UPF"
```

Pass `--pseudo-dir ~/software/pseudopotentials/pbe` to `scripts/make_qe_inputs.py`.

For new element systems, download matching PBE PAW UPF files from https://pseudopotentials.quantum-espresso.org.

## DFT workflow

DFT validates only the top few MLIP-ranked candidates. It does not replace the MLIP pipeline.

1. `scripts/select_dft_candidates.py` picks top candidates from MLIP hull scores.
2. `scripts/make_qe_inputs.py` writes pw.x input files (`pw.in` + `metadata.yaml`).
3. `scripts/run_qe_candidate.sh` runs pw.x via mpirun in a candidate folder.
4. `scripts/parse_dft_results.py` harvests energies from pw.out into a CSV.
5. `scripts/score_dft_hull.py` computes formation energies and hull distance.

Elemental reference energies in `dft/reference_energies.yaml` must use the same PBE pseudopotentials and cutoffs as the candidate calculations.
